7:610:0:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:The  topical  diagnosis  of  insulinoma  continues  to  
7:611:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:be an actual problem of modern medicine due to 
7:612:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:low  detection  rate  of  the  tumor  (about  75%)  and  
7:613:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:inconsistent  data  on  its  localization  when  using  
7:614:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:various  methods  of  visualization  (more  than  in  
7:615:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:50%  of  cases),  as  well  as  the  lack  of  a  single  diag-
7:616:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:nostic  algorithm.  In  the  clinical  practice,  many  
7:617:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:different   imaging   assessments   are   conducted,   
7:618:10:11:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:including  those  with  the  administration  of  con-
7:619:11:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:trast  agents  and  associated  with  radiation  load,  
7:620:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:as  well  as  invasive  studies,  associated  with  risk  of  
7:621:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:various  complications,  high  costs  and  duration  of  
7:622:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:the  examination.  Thus,  the  search  for  highly  sen-
7:623:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:sitive and safe methods of topical diagnosis of the 
7:624:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:insulin-producing  pancreatic  tumor  seems  rele-
7:625:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:vant.  In  the  presented  clinical  case,  the  diagnosis  
7:626:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:of  insulinoma  is  verified  by  diffusion-weighted  
7:627:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:magnetic  resonance  imaging  (DW-MRI).  It  is  an  
7:628:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:accurate  and  non-invasive  method  that  does  not  
7:629:10:10:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:involve  exposure  to  ionizing  radiation  and  does  
7:630:10:0:42:64:g_d0_f3:?:not require any administration of contrast agents. 
7:631:0:10:225:64:g_d0_f3:?:This technology, based on microstructural patho-
7:632:10:10:225:64:g_d0_f3:?:logical  changes,  allows  to  identify  small  tumors  
7:633:10:10:225:64:g_d0_f3:?:and to make a differential diagnosis of benign and 
7:634:10:10:225:64:g_d0_f3:?:malignant  neoplasms.  However,  at  present  the  
7:635:10:10:225:64:g_d0_f3:?:experience of DW-MRI use for the diagnosis of an 
7:636:10:10:225:64:g_d0_f3:?:insulin-producing  neuroendocrine  tumor  is  limit-
7:637:10:10:225:64:g_d0_f3:?:ed. Evaluation of its effectiveness in a large patient 
7:638:10:10:225:64:g_d0_f3:?:cohort would be necessary to assess the prospects 
7:639:10:16:225:64:g_d0_f3:?:for its introduction into clinical practice.
